    title: 'Magic Cat Academy – Play the Halloween Google Doodle Game',
    metaDescription: 'Play Magic Cat Academy, the Halloween Doodle where you draw spells to defeat ghosts and save Momo’s spellbook.',
    category: 'online-games',
    tags: ['arcade', 'puzzle'],
    embedUrl: 'https://html5-games.io/game/magic_cat/',
    thumbnail: '/images/magic-cat-academy.webp',
    relatedSlugs: ['google-boba-game', 'dinosaur-game', 'doodle-champion-island-games'],
    excerpt: 'Magic Cat Academy is a Halloween Google Doodle game that became so popular it spawned an entire trilogy.',
    content: `<p>Magic Cat Academy is a Halloween Google Doodle game that became so popular it spawned an entire trilogy. First released on October 30, 2016, it stars Momo — a black cat wizard student whose spellbook gets stolen by a mischievous ghost named Marshmallow. Armed with her magic wand, Momo must battle waves of ghosts to save her school and retrieve her book.</p>

<p>The gameplay is brilliantly simple: ghosts approach with symbols floating above their heads, and you defeat them by drawing those symbols on screen. Horizontal lines, vertical lines, V shapes, upside-down V shapes, and lightning bolts make up your spell arsenal. The lightning bolt is particularly satisfying — it zaps every ghost on screen at once. Occasionally a heart symbol appears, letting you restore lost health. You&#8217;ve got five lives per level, so accuracy matters as much as speed.</p>

<p>Developed by the Google Doodle team in partnership with artist Juliana Chen (who based Momo on her own real-life black cat), Magic Cat Academy features five levels set throughout the school: the library, cafeteria, classroom, gymnasium, and rooftop tower. Each level ends with a boss fight featuring a unique ghost — the Librarian Ghost, Cauldron Ghost, Planetarium Ghost, Coach Ghost, and finally Marshmallow himself, who uses Momo&#8217;s stolen spellbook to grow enormous. The difficulty ramps up steadily, with ghosts arriving faster and carrying longer symbol combinations.</p>

<p>The game proved so beloved that Google brought Momo back for Magic Cat Academy 2 in 2020 (set underwater) and Magic Cat Academy 3 in 2024 (set in space). The character even appears in the Doodle Champion Island Games. All three entries remain playable in Google&#8217;s Doodle archive.</p>

<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>How To Play Magic Cat Academy</strong></h2>

<p>Use your mouse or touchscreen to draw symbols matching those above each ghost&#8217;s head. Click and drag (or swipe on mobile) to create shapes anywhere on screen.</p>

<p>Simple spells include horizontal lines, vertical lines, and V shapes in both directions. The lightning bolt symbol damages all ghosts simultaneously — save it for crowded moments.</p>

<p>Watch for the heart symbol to appear occasionally. Drawing it restores one of your five lives.</p>

<p>Prioritise ghosts closest to Momo first. If they reach her, you lose a life. Draw smaller, confident strokes rather than large sweeping ones — the game recognises them faster.</p>

<p>Each level ends with a boss requiring multiple spell combinations. Stay calm, watch their attack patterns, and focus on accuracy over speed.</p>
<div class='code-block code-block-1' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear: both;'>

</div>
<!-- CONTENT END 1 -->`,
